---
import QuestionLayout from '@layouts/QuestionLayout.astro';

const relatedLinks = [];
const _body = "<p>The browser adapter is a Traverse placement target that runs WASM capabilities directly inside the user's browser. It uses the browser's native WebAssembly API and applies the same contract validation as every other Traverse target. The capability behaves identically whether it is called from the browser or from a server.</p>\n\n      <h2>Why run capabilities in the browser</h2>\n      <p>The main reason is consistency. If your pricing logic runs as a WASM capability on your API, you can load the same binary in the browser for instant previews. The user sees the correct number before they submit a form. No extra round-trip. No risk of the frontend computing a different result than the backend.</p>\n\n      <p>This is the core promise of Traverse placement targets. The contract is the invariant. The adapter is just where the execution happens.</p>\n\n      <h2>How it works</h2>\n      <p>The <code>traverse-expedition-wasm</code> crate compiles to a WASM binary that can itself run inside a browser. It bootstraps the Traverse runtime, loads your capability binary from a URL or bundled asset, and exposes a JavaScript API you can call from your frontend code.</p>\n\n      <ul>\n        <li>Preconditions are validated before execution, same as on the server</li>\n        <li>Postconditions are validated after the WASM function returns</li>\n        <li>The result object includes a trace artifact for debugging</li>\n        <li>Errors are typed and match the contract's error schema</li>\n      </ul>\n\n      <h2>Current status</h2>\n      <p>The local placement target is the most mature target as of v0.8.1, and since v0.8.0 the Web embedder SDK executes governed bundles directly in the browser's native WebAssembly host. Edge, cloud, and AI pipeline targets are on the roadmap. The API shape is stable but browser deployment is not yet production-ready.</p>\n\n      <p>See the <a href=\"/roadmap.html\">roadmap</a> for the planned release timeline.</p>";
const _jsonLd = "{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the browser adapter?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The browser adapter is a Traverse placement target that runs WASM capabilities inside the browser using the WebAssembly API. It applies the same contract validation as every other target, so capabilities execute identically whether the call comes from a browser, edge worker, or server.\"}}]}";
---
<QuestionLayout
  title={"What is the browser adapter?"}
  description={"The Traverse browser adapter lets you run contract-governed WASM capabilities directly in the browser. Same contracts, same behavior, zero server round-trip."}
  canonical={"https://traverse-framework.com/questions/what-is-the-browser-adapter.html"}
  category={"Getting Started"}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  jsonLd={_jsonLd}
>
  <Fragment set:html={_body} />
</QuestionLayout>
